         <blockquote>
         Heh, that's much more copacetic of you. If you weren't aiming at me, I won't aim back. Fair? ;P<P>1. Shadowbane's still in beta, and combat mechanics are among the biggest kept secrets covered under NDA, for a reason. The fact that SB's concept is supposed to blow so many minds, but we don't know how, doesn't matter in the face of that. They haven't got the shit done, minute stuff is still changing, and besides, try explaining the game mechanics of an unfinished game to someone who hasn't played it.<P>2. Their previous exploits aren't on XRG yet, but they are on <a href="http://sb.drtwister.com/interviews/bg-wolfpack.shtml" target="_blank">here.</a> The founders probably did drink a lot of beer, but they were amassing about a half-century of MUD development experience between them. I just haven't done as much work on a FAQ as some of the other XRG sites.<P>3. Not reading the story doesn't make you a jackass, but not reading the story and writing a novel about how you hadn't read it and don't care about reading it, in response to a one-line query about who /was/ reading it, crosses the line into jackassdom. Most people just say "no" when they mean "no." <img src="http://www.kaaos.com/htdocs/dcforum/Images/tongue.gif"><P>4. Wolfpack intends to make the game story an integral part of the game, which to me is as feasible as making PvP integral to the game. That's not the reason to read the story, though; it's just a good story. But you may disagree.<P>5. Most people don't really give a fuck whether anyone at Wolfpack has any business experience. It doesn't get asked very often.<P>Lately, yeah, not getting ANYTHING from Wolfpack is putting a little strain on the fansites who were expecting a sustained stream of new material, like we were getting a year ago. That shouldn't be an excuse, but when the only people who can answer the questions consistently refuse to answer them, there's not much more I can tell you.<P>However, if I were a German fansite, I'd probably get tons and tons and TONS AND TONS of material, like <a href="http://www.gamesurf.de/index.php?id=419" target="_blank">this site just did</a>.<P>J.<BR>damned vulpine<BR><a href="http://sb.xrgaming.net/" target="_blank">http://sb.xrgaming.net/</a>
